tags.name: Enchanted Woodland - Community Woodland
tags.note: Owned by the Temple Hill Trust the woodland is open all year round for the community to enjoy this green leisure space - Dartford's only openly accessible woodland.  Entrances in Cornwall Road (cobbled path and football pitch) and Marsh Street.
tags.source: Debbie Fryer, C.E.O. of the Temple Hill Trust

tags.inscription: Oakfield Park. Here on 2nd October 1886 Lord Randolph Churchill delivered his 'Dartford Speech'

tags.note: Gates closed at night, varying times at different times of year. Pedestrians can access at any time to the left of the gate (through the motorcycle barrier).

tags.information: Commemorative Gate to mark the 75th Anniversary of the end of World War II. 2020 Wilmington Society
